reviews.review: Nothing new, we already had the father bit, the falcon bumps, etc.  This was just a mashup of everything weâ€™ve already seen in a Star Wars movie before. Get the guys who wrote The Mandolorian, Rogue one to write a Star Wars movie!
Tied up the whole storyline in a neat package.  Action packed from start to finish.

The first 20 minutes was a whirlwind of explosions, fights, lasers, etc. - where's the story? Later on the movie became more interesting. Good alien creatures and satisfying ending. Is that reallly the end of Star Wars??
Great movie, lost of action scenes and an incredible ending for such historic saga!
Nice job of fixing Episode 8, but still a lot of questions and plot holes.  Overall very good!

No, this movie does not flow like a three act film. From the very start its GO GO GO! It truly feels like JJ wanted to take his vision for Episode 8 and 9, and was forced to make it all into one movie. The pacing is off but the entertainment is a great time. We see characters we've come to love from this trilogy go on one final adventure! The acting is the best of the trilogy (Especially Adam Driver) and characters from pre-Disney Star Wars make their return. While I didn't LOVE the explanations for some of the new things introduced, I can appreciate Lucasfilm and Disney for expanding the lore of this galaxy far far away. If you want a well made movie with a typical movie structure and good pacing, this isn't for you. However, if you want to see a fun, ll action, Star Wars adventure moving to close out the Skywalker Saga, this is a good movie for you.
star wars Rise of skywalker is bad movie, I like to say it was good but it was big let down this should of been endgame for star wars and it just bombs

Good movie from beginning to end but I feel this shouldn't have been the last one, a lot of things felt rushed , this felt more like a sequel than a finale,  the movie should've been 3hrs long , Not the finale on the level of Avengers endgame that I expected.  Still it was a Good movie!!
Loved it! Great way to wrap things up.

By far the best Star Wars saga movie outside of the original trilogy. The action scenes were awesome to watch and the story kept good pacing. I was pleased to see Carrie Fisher included in an appropriate and respectful way. On my way to see it a second time.
